content=["<dl>",
"<dt><a href='#Section0'>Haemorrhoids</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section0'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Rectal pain and bleeding can occur with both haemorrhoids and anal cancer, and they are often difficult to distinguish on the basis of symptoms.Physical examination reveals no palpable mass with haemorrhoids.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Biopsy is negative for malignancy in haemorrhoids.</p>",
"</dd>",
"<dt><a href='#Section1'>Rectal cancer</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section1'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Difficult to distinguish on the basis of symptoms. Rectal cancer causes a rectal mass rather than an anal mass.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Colonoscopy to identify a mass in the rectum.</p>",
"</dd>",
"<dt><a href='#Section2'>Anal margin cancer</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section2'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Indistinguishable from anal canal cancer on the basis of symptoms. On physical examination, the tumour is located in the perianal skin and does not involve the anal verge.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> No tests can differentiate anal margin cancer from anal cancer.</p>",
"</dd>",
"</dl>"].join("\n");